WEBVTT

00:10.176 --> 00:12.887
Why are you not dating anyone?

00:13.388 --> 00:14.681
I'm more comfortable alone.

00:14.764 --> 00:17.684
What inconvenienced you
when you were with someone else?

00:17.767 --> 00:19.019
Not having time for myself.

00:19.102 --> 00:21.521
-What physical characteristics…
-Thick eyebrows.

00:23.773 --> 00:26.443
Initiating personalized AI generation.

00:29.279 --> 00:31.281
Optimization complete.

01:24.459 --> 01:29.047
Congratulations on meeting Gu Yeong-il,
your custom-tailored boyfriend.

01:29.130 --> 01:29.964
Holy crap!

01:31.841 --> 01:33.510
Manager!

01:34.886 --> 01:36.179
SUBSCRIBERS: 1
A MAN JUST FOR ME

01:36.262 --> 01:37.931
I checked. There's nothing wrong.

01:38.014 --> 01:38.973
What?

01:39.599 --> 01:40.683
Excuse me.

01:43.061 --> 01:46.147
I was a bit overwhelmed,
so I may not have explained it clearly.

01:46.231 --> 01:50.068
But there's a serious defect
with his face, okay?

01:50.151 --> 01:52.362
No, he looked handsome to me.

01:52.445 --> 01:54.531
Whatever. Just make it again.

01:55.907 --> 01:57.242
-Again?
-Yes.

01:57.325 --> 02:01.162
I didn't go through over 2,000 questions
just to see that face, you know.

02:01.246 --> 02:02.831
That man…

02:03.414 --> 02:04.833
I mean, Gu Yeong-il…

02:07.252 --> 02:08.169
Anyway, no.

02:08.253 --> 02:11.089
He's been custom-tailored just for you.

02:11.172 --> 02:14.425
We threw in everything you like.

02:14.926 --> 02:17.011
Keep going.
I'm sure you'll change your mind.

02:17.095 --> 02:18.972
We have to make another one.

02:19.055 --> 02:19.889
Absolutely not.

02:20.765 --> 02:24.435
I told you, didn't I?
You can only make number 901 once.

02:25.103 --> 02:28.606
But this is a different case. His face--

02:28.690 --> 02:31.025
What's all this about his face?

02:31.109 --> 02:33.653
Is he a cyclops?
Does he have three nostrils?

02:33.736 --> 02:36.406
It's not our fault.
That's just how your ideal man looks.

02:36.489 --> 02:37.532
What?

02:37.615 --> 02:40.160
No. He's not my ideal man.

02:40.243 --> 02:41.244
That's not possible.

02:42.453 --> 02:45.540
I took those questions seriously
and answered them sincerely.

02:45.623 --> 02:47.917
We also took this very seriously.

02:48.001 --> 02:49.294
Rules are rules.

02:49.377 --> 02:50.503
No do-overs.

02:55.550 --> 02:59.012
Are they out of their damn minds?
They must be crazy!

03:07.770 --> 03:10.356
Consultations are not available
at this hour.

03:11.107 --> 03:12.609
Damn it!

03:12.692 --> 03:14.944
I mean, of all people,

03:16.029 --> 03:17.530
why did it have to be…

03:18.907 --> 03:19.908
That won't work.

03:19.991 --> 03:20.992
I like you.

03:21.075 --> 03:24.078
-I am seeing someone right now.
-All right.

03:25.788 --> 03:27.665
Why did it have to be his face?

03:27.749 --> 03:30.793
EPISODE 6
THE HYBRID MAN

03:45.308 --> 03:46.142
Hello.

03:47.560 --> 03:48.394
Hi.

03:51.814 --> 03:53.399
Doors closing.

04:17.423 --> 04:19.050
Doors opening.

04:23.596 --> 04:24.681
Aren't you getting off?

04:32.981 --> 04:35.608
You seem to value originality,
Producer Park,

04:36.192 --> 04:38.152
but this piece just doesn't hit me.

04:39.112 --> 04:42.282
It's unrefined,
but it has a clear theme and good artwork.

04:45.493 --> 04:47.495
Whoever drew this
is probably an art major.

04:48.204 --> 04:52.292
If we could refine the panel composition,
it'd be much better than it is now.

04:52.375 --> 04:55.545
I think you're suggesting
that we should look at the potential…

04:55.628 --> 04:58.631
Park Kyeong-nam is identical
to my ideal man?

04:58.715 --> 05:01.718
That's the purpose of our contest.
It's also good in the long run.

05:01.801 --> 05:03.803
There is just no way.

05:03.886 --> 05:06.639
An author with clear pros and cons
is easier to work with…

05:06.723 --> 05:07.932
But wait.

05:08.641 --> 05:10.643
I didn't know he had inner double eyelids.

05:12.061 --> 05:13.438
That's how I like them.

05:14.397 --> 05:17.317
He's also got a straight nose.

05:17.859 --> 05:20.028
And those lips…

05:31.873 --> 05:33.791
Just stop it, you crazy girl.

05:37.962 --> 05:39.213
Do you not agree?

05:39.297 --> 05:40.214
Huh?

05:41.883 --> 05:43.593
I do agree.

05:44.969 --> 05:46.179
This is good.

05:58.024 --> 05:59.359
What is up with you today?

06:01.903 --> 06:02.904
What do you mean?

06:02.987 --> 06:05.114
You jump every time
I catch you looking at me.

06:05.198 --> 06:08.451
Well, that's not…

06:08.951 --> 06:11.371
Your face was just, you know…

06:11.454 --> 06:12.497
What about my face?

06:13.081 --> 06:14.749
Your face is a bit…

06:18.127 --> 06:19.212
Is it a common face?

06:19.796 --> 06:20.630
What?

06:20.713 --> 06:25.426
I mean, it's not one of those faces
you can see just anywhere, is it?

06:26.844 --> 06:27.929
I don't understand--

06:28.012 --> 06:29.889
Food is here!

06:30.431 --> 06:31.724
Food is here!

06:32.266 --> 06:33.434
Let's eat first.

06:46.447 --> 06:49.784
Nope. No way in hell.

06:54.997 --> 06:56.165
Aren't you going to eat?

06:57.875 --> 06:58.876
Thank you.

07:06.634 --> 07:08.136
Not a chance.

07:12.807 --> 07:14.058
That one's mine.

07:18.896 --> 07:21.107
Well, sorry about that.

07:27.071 --> 07:29.449
Is the world pranking me right now?

07:33.536 --> 07:34.537
Damn it!

07:48.134 --> 07:49.510
I'm getting this one too.

07:51.387 --> 07:54.056
Just stop.
How are you even splurging at a bookstore?

07:54.140 --> 07:56.559
I can't buy clothes now.
Might as well get some books.

07:56.642 --> 07:58.436
I bought stuff for my blind date,

07:58.519 --> 08:01.022
and my credit card bills
are gonna get me evicted.

08:01.105 --> 08:02.773
A blind date? So soon?

08:03.357 --> 08:05.526
"So soon"? I've been single for ages.

08:05.610 --> 08:06.694
Has it been two weeks?

08:07.987 --> 08:10.531
Exactly. I should get back out there.

08:10.615 --> 08:12.492
I've got two dates tomorrow.

08:13.242 --> 08:15.036
Oh, this is great.

08:15.119 --> 08:18.664
Why don't you look for a guy
to set me up with?

08:18.748 --> 08:20.625
You just said you have two dates tomorrow.

08:20.708 --> 08:24.420
Hey, don't you know people read
multiple books at the same time now?

08:24.504 --> 08:26.964
No one goes around
seeing just one guy at a time.

08:29.091 --> 08:30.927
Kim…

08:31.010 --> 08:32.094
Kim Yeong-hun.

08:32.178 --> 08:34.680
He has a girlfriend? Since when?

08:35.723 --> 08:38.309
Anyone from Naemo?

08:39.060 --> 08:39.977
Park Kyeong…

08:40.061 --> 08:41.812
Huh? You're already at Park?

08:41.896 --> 08:46.275
Seo Hyeon-uk also has a girlfriend, and…

08:46.359 --> 08:47.527
Jeong-sik.

08:47.610 --> 08:48.694
He has a child?

08:48.778 --> 08:50.071
I think she goes to school.

08:50.154 --> 08:51.155
Cute.

08:53.282 --> 08:54.659
What? Is that it?

08:55.618 --> 08:56.869
There isn't a single guy?

08:57.995 --> 08:59.914
Just what I thought.

08:59.997 --> 09:00.831
Hey.

09:01.541 --> 09:03.084
When did everyone get snapped up?

09:04.126 --> 09:06.796
Why so surprised?
You're not even interested in dating.

09:07.922 --> 09:10.091
Things have been this bad for a while now.

09:12.927 --> 09:15.137
Does that mean
all the decent men are taken,

09:16.847 --> 09:18.891
even if I wanted to date one?

09:26.566 --> 09:28.484
Things will be different this holiday.

09:34.657 --> 09:36.284
Because you'll have…

09:41.330 --> 09:43.916
Boyfriend on Demand next to you.

09:58.931 --> 10:01.350
Fine. I'll fall for it.

10:02.101 --> 10:03.436
Just this once.

10:32.131 --> 10:33.382
Your engine's totally shot.

10:34.759 --> 10:35.760
Excuse me?

10:35.843 --> 10:38.763
I saw the smoke and followed you.
Where are you headed?

10:39.472 --> 10:40.890
Oh, I…

10:42.725 --> 10:44.018
I don't know.

10:44.602 --> 10:46.979
I was just driving along this road.

10:48.522 --> 10:49.357
Are you a tourist?

10:51.150 --> 10:51.984
A tourist?

11:08.042 --> 11:09.585
Follow me if you want.

11:10.878 --> 11:14.465
"What's the most romantic first encounter
you've ever dreamed of?"

11:14.548 --> 11:18.052
Going on a trip
and meeting a guy with a free spirit

11:18.135 --> 11:20.971
at an unfamiliar place,
just like in a movie.

11:22.390 --> 11:24.141
It's dangerous here at night.

11:26.602 --> 11:29.397
-You want me to get on that?
-Then are you going to stay here?

11:30.523 --> 11:32.775
No, thanks. I'm scared.

11:47.289 --> 11:49.875
Before I even realized it, I got on.

12:05.474 --> 12:06.475
This feels weird.

12:07.351 --> 12:11.856
I'm riding behind a stranger
who looks just like Park Kyeong-nam,

12:12.440 --> 12:15.359
and I don't even know
where we're going, so why…

12:17.528 --> 12:20.865
Why is his back so comfy
that it feels like it was made for me?

12:31.917 --> 12:33.586
And the wind, it's so…

12:40.634 --> 12:42.470
It's so perfect.

12:45.264 --> 12:46.515
And his smell…

12:54.899 --> 12:55.858
How nice.

13:03.908 --> 13:05.242
What is this feeling?

13:21.091 --> 13:22.510
-Come on in.
-Yeong-il.

13:35.314 --> 13:36.315
Hi.

13:38.776 --> 13:41.946
Why is everything so detailed?
It feels so real.

13:53.791 --> 13:54.625
Oh my God.

13:55.251 --> 13:56.752
Bartender. Yeong-il's friend.

13:56.836 --> 13:59.338
People get scared when they first see me.
I don't bite though.

14:00.506 --> 14:01.882
I've seen you before.

14:02.967 --> 14:04.718
You really startled me!

14:06.679 --> 14:09.223
I'll have my usual, and for her--

14:09.306 --> 14:11.475
Hold up. Let me guess.

14:36.375 --> 14:38.043
-No way.
-Is it to your liking?

14:39.211 --> 14:41.380
-Totally.
-Just holler when you're done.

14:44.216 --> 14:45.634
What brings you here all alone?

14:46.468 --> 14:49.388
You know,
I just needed to get my life in order.

14:51.515 --> 14:54.184
Actually,
I recently went through a breakup.

14:55.603 --> 14:56.437
May I ask why?

14:57.521 --> 14:58.480
He was a cheater.

14:59.565 --> 15:00.649
He met another woman?

15:01.901 --> 15:02.735
Try 10,000.

15:07.031 --> 15:08.032
Say what?

15:09.491 --> 15:10.743
Ten thousand women.

15:19.126 --> 15:23.422
This is the dining area.
You can have coffee in there anytime.

15:24.673 --> 15:25.674
Thank you.

15:26.759 --> 15:30.512
You can sleep in that room.
I'll give the owner a heads-up.

15:31.096 --> 15:31.972
Here.

15:35.851 --> 15:37.353
It was nice meeting you today.

15:54.703 --> 15:55.579
Su-ji?

15:56.080 --> 15:57.915
Hey, Su-ji!

15:57.998 --> 16:00.668
It's been so long! How have you been?

16:02.252 --> 16:03.587
Mind your manners.

16:05.798 --> 16:07.007
Do you know me?

16:07.091 --> 16:08.884
Yu-ra, a Korean tourist.

16:11.637 --> 16:12.888
I used to.

16:12.972 --> 16:15.432
Actually, no. I don't know you.

16:15.516 --> 16:18.644
Looks like another weirdo has joined us.

16:23.023 --> 16:25.275
Please don't close that door.

16:25.776 --> 16:28.320
That door is broken, okay?

16:28.821 --> 16:30.155
Once it closes,

16:31.532 --> 16:32.533
it won't open.

16:34.118 --> 16:35.619
Didn't know. Sorry, honey.

16:37.496 --> 16:38.956
I still don't like your tone.

16:39.456 --> 16:40.666
Hey, mister!

16:41.375 --> 16:43.252
Who the hell brought this woman here?

16:46.005 --> 16:48.132
I liked her best when she was Su-ji.

16:48.924 --> 16:50.676
She's even worse than Ms. Choi.

17:05.357 --> 17:07.359
I can't believe
he brought me to his hostel.

17:09.778 --> 17:10.612
Wait.

17:11.780 --> 17:14.450
He's not going to barge in here, is he?

17:18.203 --> 17:19.872
Aren't you coming to dinner?

17:21.415 --> 17:22.499
Coming!

17:31.175 --> 17:33.343
Goddamn it!

17:34.219 --> 17:36.555
This stuff is tasteless.

17:38.515 --> 17:39.641
I'm done eating.

17:46.106 --> 17:47.107
A tough roommate, huh?

17:48.358 --> 17:49.443
Yeah.

17:50.319 --> 17:52.404
Your car will be here
the morning after next.

17:53.072 --> 17:54.448
All right. Thanks.

17:57.493 --> 18:00.662
By the way, what do you do for a living?

18:02.581 --> 18:03.415
I draw.

18:03.499 --> 18:04.500
What?

18:05.125 --> 18:05.959
You draw?

18:08.003 --> 18:09.171
So you're an artist?

18:10.422 --> 18:12.508
I just travel around and draw what I like.

18:13.592 --> 18:14.635
Mi-rae.

18:14.718 --> 18:17.054
It's your turn now.
What's your dream guy like?

18:17.137 --> 18:18.305
My dream guy?

18:18.388 --> 18:20.307
Gang Dong-won for me. Ju Ji-hoon for her.

18:24.186 --> 18:25.020
For me,

18:25.896 --> 18:27.231
it's a hybrid man.

18:28.482 --> 18:30.609
-What's that?
-Look.

18:31.610 --> 18:35.114
Someone calm and pure at heart,

18:35.197 --> 18:37.533
with a genuine love for art.

18:45.207 --> 18:48.127
I've been playing ball.
You're studying during break time?

18:48.210 --> 18:50.629
But at the same time,
I want him to be wild and free.

18:51.880 --> 18:53.382
What is she talking about?

18:53.465 --> 18:55.092
What I'm saying is…

18:55.175 --> 18:58.762
It's like when you mix a little red
into white to get this subtle…

18:59.263 --> 19:02.474
-You get me, don't you?
-No. What is he, Santa Claus?

19:03.559 --> 19:04.685
Anyway…

19:07.229 --> 19:08.814
that's my dream guy.

19:10.482 --> 19:11.316
Both…

19:13.694 --> 19:17.364
We threw in everything you like.

19:20.784 --> 19:22.035
They made it work?

19:31.712 --> 19:33.130
-Hello.
-Hi.

19:44.349 --> 19:46.852
The heart just cannot lie, you know.

19:47.811 --> 19:50.230
It's dead silent
if you don't like a person.

19:50.856 --> 19:53.775
-You know what I mean, right?
-What are you getting at?

19:53.859 --> 19:55.527
I want to act cool about it,

19:55.611 --> 19:58.822
but whenever I think about him,
my heart just goes…

20:00.073 --> 20:01.074
And then…

20:02.075 --> 20:03.160
You know?

20:03.243 --> 20:06.288
Man, she's got it bad.
What kind of guy did you set her up with?

20:06.371 --> 20:09.833
He does have a way of sucking women in
like a swamp, but…

20:09.917 --> 20:12.252
If he hasn't contacted you in a week,
it's over.

20:12.336 --> 20:13.587
What is your problem?

20:13.670 --> 20:17.382
You should really try that thing.
To calm yourself down.

20:18.467 --> 20:20.385
-Nah, I'm good.
-Try what?

20:20.469 --> 20:22.137
-Boyfriend on Demand.
-Huh?

20:22.721 --> 20:24.890
Do people actually do Boyfriend on Demand?

20:26.266 --> 20:27.434
Really?

20:27.517 --> 20:30.520
-I thought it was all just marketing.
-So did I.

20:30.604 --> 20:33.941
I can hardly put money aside
with a tiny salary like mine.

20:34.024 --> 20:36.485
Who could afford to subscribe to that?

20:36.568 --> 20:38.528
A lot of my friends are subscribed to it.

20:38.612 --> 20:39.613
No way.

20:39.696 --> 20:40.697
No way!

20:40.781 --> 20:42.366
It's true. Think about it.

20:42.449 --> 20:46.620
Dating makes us spend so much money
and deal with an awful lot of stress.

20:46.703 --> 20:48.997
It saves you all that trouble.
How great is that?

20:49.081 --> 20:51.875
Besides, nowadays,
just by fangirling over idols,

20:51.959 --> 20:53.752
you spend that much every month.

20:54.253 --> 20:55.545
You do have a point.

20:56.463 --> 20:58.632
The world is doomed. It really is.

21:00.550 --> 21:01.927
That's a bit harsh.

21:02.010 --> 21:05.013
Now that I think about it,
was it 500,000 won?

21:06.390 --> 21:07.891
Right. 500,000.

21:07.975 --> 21:11.144
Okay. I do spend that much on eating out,

21:11.228 --> 21:14.898
watching movies,
going on trips and drives, and so on.

21:23.365 --> 21:26.368
As I thought, no reaction at all.

21:26.451 --> 21:28.787
Hey, you try contacting him.

21:30.664 --> 21:33.292
Go ahead, text him.
Does he ever talk about me?

21:34.376 --> 21:35.460
That's right.

21:35.544 --> 21:40.424
The guy I met yesterday and Kyeong-nam
are two completely different people.

21:54.813 --> 21:55.814
So different.

22:00.402 --> 22:01.486
Cheers.

22:07.451 --> 22:08.285
Aren't you bored?

22:09.745 --> 22:10.579
Nope.

22:11.371 --> 22:13.874
You've just been sitting here.
Anything caught your eye?

22:16.460 --> 22:17.461
You.

22:29.556 --> 22:32.476
This isn't a chair, you know.
Don't just sit on it.

22:35.854 --> 22:37.272
Are you having fun now?

22:37.356 --> 22:38.190
Yes.

22:38.940 --> 22:39.983
Let's go.

22:40.484 --> 22:41.485
There we go!

23:10.389 --> 23:11.556
Chaturanga.

23:12.599 --> 23:13.433
Head up.

23:20.232 --> 23:22.567
Lift your body and move into downward dog.

23:22.651 --> 23:23.652
Downward dog.

23:23.735 --> 23:25.821
Keep your heels on the floor.

23:25.904 --> 23:27.072
Okay.

23:27.155 --> 23:29.074
-Back to Chaturanga.
-Back to Chaturanga.

23:29.157 --> 23:30.909
Lift your head again,

23:30.992 --> 23:31.910
open your heart--

23:31.993 --> 23:34.329
Open my heart? Let me get a little closer.

23:34.413 --> 23:36.706
No, not like that. I meant exhale.

23:41.420 --> 23:42.421
How's that?

23:43.922 --> 23:44.756
Let go!

23:44.840 --> 23:46.925
Shut your mouth and breathe.

23:47.008 --> 23:48.927
-Stop!
-You need to breathe.

23:49.010 --> 23:51.430
-Let me go!
-Hamstring! Breathe!

23:56.977 --> 23:59.438
What's this? You've only drawn couples.

24:00.772 --> 24:02.691
I didn't feel like drawing other subjects.

24:04.401 --> 24:08.488
An artist who only draws couples.
How interesting.

24:09.906 --> 24:13.160
I don't draw just any couple I see.
I have standards.

24:16.204 --> 24:19.958
Those who don't doubt the future
and focus on the love in front of them.

24:20.542 --> 24:21.585
That's who I draw.

24:23.503 --> 24:24.337
Why is that?

24:25.130 --> 24:26.131
I don't know.

24:29.509 --> 24:31.678
Because it's sad when love changes.

24:34.681 --> 24:36.183
That must be why I record them.

24:44.566 --> 24:46.943
Let's go back.
The sun's going to set soon.

24:52.324 --> 24:53.366
What to do?

24:54.451 --> 24:55.285
Huh?

24:56.328 --> 24:59.414
I wasn't going to say anything,
but I'll be honest with you.

25:01.791 --> 25:02.626
About what?

25:02.709 --> 25:03.668
I think we're lost.

25:04.461 --> 25:05.295
What now?

25:15.055 --> 25:18.767
Stop messing with me.
I know you know the way.

25:19.518 --> 25:20.477
I'm serious.

25:20.977 --> 25:24.856
Yu-ra told me that a couple of newlyweds
went missing around here recently.

25:32.572 --> 25:34.491
What's your favorite movie genre?

25:35.825 --> 25:37.744
HORROR (OCCULT HORROR ESPECIALLY!)

25:37.827 --> 25:38.787
Those bastards.

25:39.287 --> 25:41.790
I said I liked to watch it,
not experience it!

25:42.290 --> 25:45.043
I don't like it here, okay? I hate it.

25:45.126 --> 25:46.127
Let's go…

26:02.394 --> 26:03.353
It's the owner's dog.

26:04.521 --> 26:05.605
Oh, I see.

26:07.732 --> 26:08.608
Are you that scared?

26:09.776 --> 26:12.112
No, well… just a little?

26:13.947 --> 26:15.240
I guess it is a bit dark.

26:40.473 --> 26:41.308
Not anymore.

27:04.331 --> 27:07.042
Keep going.
I'm sure you'll change your mind.

27:07.792 --> 27:09.210
Calm down.

27:09.753 --> 27:11.254
Calm down, for crying out loud!

27:13.757 --> 27:15.342
Doors closing.

27:25.101 --> 27:26.686
Doors opening.

27:27.854 --> 27:29.731
Excuse me. Coming through.

27:29.814 --> 27:31.691
Sorry. Excuse me.

27:32.734 --> 27:34.944
Sorry about that. I'm sorry.

27:35.028 --> 27:36.863
Doors closing.

27:47.916 --> 27:49.417
Seo Mi-rae, come to my office.

27:50.251 --> 27:52.837
Hey, Kyeong-nam, you too.

27:54.047 --> 27:55.882
Did you talk to Yun Song?

27:56.466 --> 27:58.718
Sorry? About what?

27:59.302 --> 28:01.429
Kyeong-nam said he told you.

28:02.514 --> 28:05.433
Hwany will be doing
the home appliance commercial.

28:06.851 --> 28:07.727
You didn't tell her?

28:08.687 --> 28:11.189
I'm sorry, sir. I'll tell her right away.

28:11.773 --> 28:13.858
Too late now! She would go berserk and…

28:13.942 --> 28:15.151
I can't even…

28:16.444 --> 28:20.281
That's that. You're supposed to attend
the BCF with Yun Song, aren't you?

28:20.365 --> 28:22.534
Take Kyeong-nam and Hwany with you.

28:23.743 --> 28:26.246
-What?
-I called you here to tell you that.

28:27.622 --> 28:29.708
Both of them were nominated this time.

28:30.667 --> 28:32.585
-Hwany too?
-That's right.

28:33.169 --> 28:36.381
And I get the feeling
at least one of them will win something.

28:36.464 --> 28:38.341
So take good care of your authors.

28:38.967 --> 28:39.926
Understand?

28:40.009 --> 28:40.844
Yes, sir.

28:41.469 --> 28:42.303
Yes, sir.

28:51.020 --> 28:52.230
So…

28:54.691 --> 28:57.444
Please tell Ms. Yun about it.
She won't take it well.

28:59.028 --> 29:01.197
Don't worry. I'll try to soften the blow.

29:01.865 --> 29:02.991
Ms. Seo.

29:03.908 --> 29:04.909
Yes?

29:07.871 --> 29:08.830
Why do you do that?

29:10.206 --> 29:11.958
What… do you mean?

29:12.876 --> 29:15.044
You're avoiding me
when I'm the one who got rejected.

29:18.298 --> 29:20.175
I never did that. When did I do that?

29:21.259 --> 29:23.261
I know you're uncomfortable around me,

29:24.637 --> 29:26.222
but could you try not to show it?

29:29.517 --> 29:31.060
This is upsetting for me as well.

29:47.535 --> 29:49.287
Hey, are you insane?

29:49.370 --> 29:50.747
Why did that go to him?

29:50.830 --> 29:53.625
Well, the advertiser requested it.

29:53.708 --> 29:57.420
They chose to deliver their ads
with his shitty drawings and not mine?

29:57.504 --> 29:58.755
Have they gone cuckoo?

29:58.838 --> 29:59.964
Ms. Yun,

30:00.048 --> 30:02.217
I'll make sure to find you a better ad--

30:04.219 --> 30:05.261
She hung up on me.

30:06.888 --> 30:08.890
God, this is so annoying!

30:15.688 --> 30:17.690
You all know
IG is the best brand there is.

30:18.191 --> 30:20.860
Coming soon,
PlanC and IG's collab webtoon.

30:20.944 --> 30:22.028
I'll do my best!

30:22.111 --> 30:24.113
Let's make PlanC number one!

30:24.197 --> 30:25.281
"Number one"?

30:25.949 --> 30:27.659
Why, that little prick…

30:36.167 --> 30:38.419
KOREAN BEEF INTESTINES

30:39.420 --> 30:40.421
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

30:44.676 --> 30:47.011
I'm so sick of greasy food
from all my blind dates.

30:49.514 --> 30:50.598
That's more like it.

30:50.682 --> 30:51.975
Did your dates go well?

30:53.017 --> 30:54.561
It was a disaster.

30:54.644 --> 30:56.729
Two dates in one day was a stretch.

30:56.813 --> 31:00.400
Their paths crossed, and somehow,
my dates ran into each other.

31:02.443 --> 31:04.529
I knew you were going to mess up.

31:04.612 --> 31:07.782
But the thing is, I went on another date
a few days after that.

31:09.951 --> 31:12.120
The nerve of that guy!

31:12.787 --> 31:16.124
He kept pushing me about whether my salary
started with a three or a four.

31:16.207 --> 31:17.083
Wow.

31:17.166 --> 31:19.961
How the hell is that any of his business?

31:20.044 --> 31:22.088
Do you know what he texted me
the next day?

31:22.755 --> 31:26.134
"I was deeply moved by your story
of trying to find your true self."

31:26.217 --> 31:28.261
"I hope you find the right person."

31:28.344 --> 31:29.554
Wow.

31:29.637 --> 31:32.932
It was like an HR text to a candidate
who failed a job interview.

31:33.016 --> 31:35.977
And I never signed up for an interview!
Are you kidding me?

31:36.060 --> 31:39.355
Jeez, then just stop
going on those blind dates.

31:39.439 --> 31:40.940
All they do is make you mad.

31:41.024 --> 31:44.819
You also saw for yourself last time.
There are no decent men left out there.

31:45.862 --> 31:49.782
You and I are the birds
that overslept way too much.

31:49.866 --> 31:55.038
We have to start foraging for crumbs
that the early birds left behind.

31:55.121 --> 31:57.874
Do we really have to stoop
to looking for crumbs?

31:59.500 --> 32:00.335
Hey.

32:01.085 --> 32:03.588
Are you trying to say
that I'm obsessed with men?

32:03.671 --> 32:06.049
Hey, that's not what I meant.

32:06.132 --> 32:07.550
Then what did you mean?

32:07.634 --> 32:10.803
"Can you not live without men?
I'm sick of all your men talk."

32:10.887 --> 32:11.930
That's it, no?

32:12.013 --> 32:14.766
Hey, it's only because
that's all you've been talking about.

32:14.849 --> 32:18.561
And you've never talked to me about men?
What about that guy from your office?

32:19.395 --> 32:22.148
Seriously? He's just one of my colleagues.

32:22.231 --> 32:25.610
You've been talking about him
an awful lot these last few months.

32:26.194 --> 32:27.570
What? I have not!

32:27.654 --> 32:29.864
I mean, definitely not that much.

32:32.408 --> 32:36.162
I was gonna wait until you told me first,
but I can't do this anymore.

32:36.245 --> 32:37.246
You like him, don't you?

32:38.790 --> 32:41.292
Hey, are you insane? No, I don't!

32:47.090 --> 32:48.508
It's the other way around.

32:48.591 --> 32:50.927
The other way around? What does that mean?

32:51.844 --> 32:52.929
Well,

32:53.763 --> 32:55.932
he asked me out.

32:57.517 --> 32:58.351
Hey!

33:01.062 --> 33:03.648
Why are you dropping this bomb on me now?

33:03.731 --> 33:04.857
When was this?

33:04.941 --> 33:08.069
It's been a while,
and I already turned him down.

33:10.279 --> 33:11.614
That can't be!

33:12.573 --> 33:14.200
Why do you keep saying that?

33:14.867 --> 33:16.703
Something's not right.

33:17.787 --> 33:19.372
Show me a picture of that guy.

33:19.455 --> 33:23.126
I don't have one. He's not on Instagram.
He doesn't even have a profile picture.

33:24.127 --> 33:27.547
Can I please borrow your phone?
I really need to keep filming.

33:31.884 --> 33:32.719
Let's see.

33:34.846 --> 33:35.805
-Give it.
-Here.

33:41.102 --> 33:42.145
What the heck?

33:42.937 --> 33:43.771
What?

33:45.732 --> 33:48.526
-He's definitely not your type.
-What?

33:48.609 --> 33:52.113
He is good-looking,
but not Seo Mi-rae's type.

33:52.697 --> 33:56.451
You're into guys who are laid-back.
This guy looks too uptight.

33:57.452 --> 33:58.286
Really?

33:59.704 --> 34:00.538
Right?

34:01.205 --> 34:03.791
Yeah, that's what I'm talking about.

34:04.375 --> 34:05.460
Cheers!

34:06.461 --> 34:07.295
Cheers.

34:12.216 --> 34:13.301
I knew it.

34:14.302 --> 34:15.511
He's not the one.

34:49.670 --> 34:50.505
You're here.

34:51.422 --> 34:52.381
Yes.

34:56.052 --> 34:56.886
Well…

34:58.805 --> 34:59.639
Your hair.

35:03.059 --> 35:06.062
It must've gotten there
while I was picking this up for Ms. Yun.

35:07.605 --> 35:09.023
Congratulations in advance.

35:09.524 --> 35:13.319
She might not get it,
but I got this just in case she does.

35:13.402 --> 35:17.115
I hope there's good news for Hwany too.

35:18.741 --> 35:19.826
I hope so too.

35:24.872 --> 35:25.706
Oh…

35:26.457 --> 35:27.291
Ms. Seo?

35:28.167 --> 35:30.169
About what I said last time…

35:31.129 --> 35:32.547
Don't worry about it too much.

35:36.467 --> 35:37.552
I'm fine.

35:42.390 --> 35:43.474
Let's head in.

35:48.062 --> 35:52.984
We will now begin the awards ceremony
for the 27th Busan Comics Festival!

35:59.699 --> 36:03.411
There is no greater honor
than earning the fans' love.

36:03.494 --> 36:06.372
In that sense,
this is a very meaningful award.

36:06.455 --> 36:11.377
With an overwhelming number of fan votes,
the Popularity Award goes to…

36:12.378 --> 36:13.254
Congratulations.

36:13.337 --> 36:16.883
Yun Song, author of The Man to Know.
Congratulations!

36:20.428 --> 36:22.138
-Congratulations!
-Thank you.

36:22.221 --> 36:24.640
…a romance between a chaebol heir
and a hotelier.

36:24.724 --> 36:27.226
With its charming characters
and an engaging plot,

36:27.310 --> 36:28.811
it has received a lot of love…

36:28.895 --> 36:30.062
Congratulations.

36:30.146 --> 36:31.147
Congratulations!

36:31.647 --> 36:35.151
POPULARITY AWARD
YUN SONG, THE MAN TO KNOW

36:35.234 --> 36:36.068
All right.

36:36.152 --> 36:38.654
For a while now,

36:38.738 --> 36:41.866
the Popularity Award
is all you've been giving me.

36:44.535 --> 36:48.706
I guess I should be thanking you
for giving me anything at all, right?

36:50.583 --> 36:53.377
But if you give me this award again
next year,

36:53.961 --> 36:55.963
I'm seriously going to stop coming.

37:03.304 --> 37:05.723
I'm just kidding. Oh my God!

37:06.349 --> 37:07.433
Okay.

37:07.516 --> 37:08.351
Thank you.

37:14.232 --> 37:18.653
Next, for bringing a breath of fresh air
into the comics industry,

37:18.736 --> 37:20.655
the New Artist Award goes to…

37:21.155 --> 37:22.990
Congratulations, Hwasubun.

37:23.699 --> 37:24.867
Congratulations.

37:26.577 --> 37:30.623
Not Okay, a story about student athletes
who fall into a dungeon in another world,

37:30.706 --> 37:33.960
was praised for its cheeky perspective
and bold expressiveness.

37:34.043 --> 37:35.586
Congratulations!

37:39.840 --> 37:41.050
Moving on.

37:41.133 --> 37:44.011
-It's okay.
-This one's for Webtoon of the Year.

37:44.095 --> 37:47.265
Only one will rise above the competition
to claim this honor.

37:47.348 --> 37:48.683
Which one will it be?

37:49.267 --> 37:51.936
I will now announce the winner
of Webtoon of the Year.

37:52.019 --> 37:56.524
The winner of Webtoon of the Year
at the 27th Busan Comics Festival is…

37:58.859 --> 38:01.946
Hwany's PlanC. Congratulations!

38:04.949 --> 38:05.866
Congratulations!

38:06.826 --> 38:07.660
It's really me?

38:08.286 --> 38:10.913
PlanC is a black comedy about young people

38:10.997 --> 38:14.709
chasing a new life in the countryside,
drawn into a mysterious incident.

38:14.792 --> 38:18.879
With its solid direction, clear theme,
and high-quality plot,

38:18.963 --> 38:21.382
it has captivated
readers and critics alike.

38:21.465 --> 38:22.300
Congratulations.

38:22.383 --> 38:24.927
Congratulations on your award!

38:26.512 --> 38:27.513
Thank you.

38:30.057 --> 38:34.562
I had no idea I'd be presented
such a big award, so--

38:34.645 --> 38:35.938
You're so handsome!

38:36.022 --> 38:36.856
Thank you.

38:36.939 --> 38:38.691
You call that handsome?

38:38.774 --> 38:40.609
I don't know what to say.

38:40.693 --> 38:41.944
Don't cry!

38:42.028 --> 38:44.864
Kyeong-nam, who has helped me a lot
since the very start,

38:44.947 --> 38:46.866
Director Hwang Byeong-hak,

38:46.949 --> 38:49.618
Producer Cho Min-seok,
who was my editor for a long time,

38:49.702 --> 38:50.828
and everyone else who…

38:50.911 --> 38:52.455
I'm seriously ticked off.

38:52.538 --> 38:53.748
…I am grateful.

38:53.831 --> 38:56.083
I'd like to share this award
with all of you.

38:56.167 --> 38:57.084
Thank you!

38:57.168 --> 38:58.753
You deserve it!

39:04.467 --> 39:05.551
Let me go!

39:05.634 --> 39:08.012
You came all this way,
and this is how you act?

39:08.095 --> 39:09.597
Hey, I said no!

39:10.181 --> 39:11.474
Seriously.

39:11.557 --> 39:12.391
Hey.

39:12.475 --> 39:14.935
I didn't come all the way here
to be used as a prop.

39:15.019 --> 39:16.896
Thank you! Yes.

39:18.647 --> 39:20.316
How could you put it that way?

39:20.399 --> 39:24.236
He works on the same platform as you.
Why can't you just congratulate him?

39:24.987 --> 39:27.656
When are you ever going to grow up?

39:29.492 --> 39:31.160
Last time, you asked me

39:31.243 --> 39:34.580
if I was going to let a kid claw his way
onto the same day as me.

39:36.290 --> 39:37.666
Come on, let's just go inside.

39:37.750 --> 39:38.918
-Let go.
-Please!

39:39.001 --> 39:40.669
Let go of me. I mean it!

39:41.337 --> 39:42.171
Seo Mi-rae!

40:05.611 --> 40:06.529
Are you okay?

40:09.156 --> 40:10.950
Yes. I'm okay.

40:12.618 --> 40:13.452
Ms. Yun.

40:14.328 --> 40:16.247
Why are you out here? Let's go inside.

40:17.665 --> 40:20.376
This is so annoying, seriously.

40:31.095 --> 40:33.264
It's all thanks to you guys. Thank you!

40:36.350 --> 40:39.270
-The drink hits different tonight.
-Congratulations!

40:39.353 --> 40:41.105
What? Thank you, guys!

40:42.189 --> 40:43.983
Flowers, really? You keep it.

40:47.486 --> 40:48.654
Let's take a picture.

40:48.737 --> 40:49.738
-Sure!
-Sounds good.

40:49.822 --> 40:52.158
Okay. One, two…

40:53.200 --> 40:55.453
-Cheers!
-Congratulations.

40:55.995 --> 40:57.538
Congratulations!

41:04.378 --> 41:06.380
Hey, you said
you couldn't eat uncooked food.

41:09.508 --> 41:10.843
I'm gonna start trying it today.

41:11.510 --> 41:12.344
Yeah?

41:13.095 --> 41:13.929
Ms. Yun.

41:14.013 --> 41:16.932
I would love to treat you today.
Let's grab some whiskey.

41:17.016 --> 41:18.767
-Wow!
-You're the man!

41:19.685 --> 41:21.187
Something super expensive?

41:21.270 --> 41:22.188
Of course!

41:22.271 --> 41:23.189
All right!

41:24.982 --> 41:26.567
I need to take this.

41:28.694 --> 41:29.528
Hello?

41:30.112 --> 41:33.282
What is this? How did you know to call me?

41:33.365 --> 41:35.451
We're having an after-party right now.

41:35.534 --> 41:38.120
Wow, thank you. I appreciate it.

41:38.204 --> 41:40.039
Let's grab a meal when I'm in Seoul.

41:40.122 --> 41:41.916
Yes, Mr. Cho. Have a good night!

41:42.875 --> 41:43.709
Mr. Cho?

41:44.335 --> 41:46.128
Producer Cho called you?

41:46.670 --> 41:47.546
Give me your phone.

41:47.630 --> 41:49.590
Why? What's this about?

41:49.673 --> 41:51.383
Damn it, seriously.

41:52.384 --> 41:54.011
I can't believe this.

41:55.095 --> 41:56.514
The person you have dialed is…

41:56.597 --> 41:59.433
Why is it that every time I call him,
it doesn't go through?

42:00.601 --> 42:01.852
He must be busy right now.

42:02.853 --> 42:04.522
Ms. Yun, calm down for a second.

42:04.605 --> 42:05.523
Hey.

42:05.606 --> 42:08.359
Why does that bastard call you
and act all nice to you

42:08.442 --> 42:10.444
but leave my calls unanswered for months?

42:10.528 --> 42:12.029
How on earth would I know that?

42:12.112 --> 42:14.240
Why did he block me
but stay in touch with you?

42:14.323 --> 42:16.575
Maybe you were a fucking pain in the ass!

42:20.079 --> 42:20.913
What?

42:20.996 --> 42:23.082
That's not what I…

42:23.165 --> 42:25.334
-Ms. Yun.
-Get a load of this guy.

42:25.417 --> 42:27.753
I've had enough of your shit.

42:27.836 --> 42:31.840
Hey, you're scheming with Cho
to get back at me, aren't you?

42:32.716 --> 42:35.219
I heard he went to Director Hwang
and made a fuss

42:35.302 --> 42:37.596
about how he was treating us differently.

42:37.680 --> 42:41.100
Did you ask to have your upload day moved
so you can screw me over?

42:41.183 --> 42:43.269
That's got nothing to do with this!

42:43.352 --> 42:45.145
That's not true, Ms. Yun.

42:45.229 --> 42:47.731
Mr. Hwang decides
matters regarding releases, after all.

42:49.441 --> 42:51.944
This is hilarious. Hey, then did you…

42:54.029 --> 42:55.447
No, wait.

42:55.531 --> 42:58.867
I honestly wasn't going to bring this up.

42:59.618 --> 43:00.452
What?

43:01.870 --> 43:03.163
Are you not over me yet?

43:08.711 --> 43:09.753
What?

43:11.088 --> 43:14.425
When Cho got us a studio in Hapjeong-dong,

43:14.508 --> 43:17.886
you were the one who secretly left snacks
in front of my room.

43:17.970 --> 43:21.599
I saw you run away to the basement
after leaving them several times.

43:22.558 --> 43:24.560
Hold it right there. That was…

43:24.643 --> 43:27.229
Hey, you just got rejected, that's all.

43:27.313 --> 43:30.316
Did you really have to hold a grudge
and screw me over?

43:30.941 --> 43:32.359
That's so petty of you.

43:33.444 --> 43:35.362
-Not true.
-What? Did Cho tell you?

43:35.446 --> 43:37.865
That I threw it all out
without even trying it?

43:37.948 --> 43:39.450
Unbelievable.

43:39.950 --> 43:41.452
Those…

43:42.786 --> 43:43.746
Those were…

43:43.829 --> 43:45.039
What?

43:46.290 --> 43:47.791
Those were meant for So-yeong!

43:51.670 --> 43:52.671
Who is So-yeong?

43:56.175 --> 43:57.092
Your assistant?

44:01.847 --> 44:05.184
Ms. Yun? We get it for now.

44:05.934 --> 44:07.144
It's spilling over.

44:09.438 --> 44:11.357
Hang on. I need to go to the bathroom.

44:12.149 --> 44:13.108
Let her through.

44:17.655 --> 44:18.739
What just happened?

44:22.159 --> 44:25.663
You know, I'm not the type
to make things up in my head.

44:26.455 --> 44:30.376
Given the situation back then,
this misunderstanding was inevitable.

44:30.459 --> 44:33.128
I'll bet anyone would have thought
the same.

44:33.212 --> 44:35.214
-Totally.
-Of course.

44:37.633 --> 44:40.260
I'm really not like that. Okay?

44:41.261 --> 44:42.554
I have a boyfriend.

44:42.638 --> 44:44.473
I have a boyfriend!

44:44.556 --> 44:45.808
-Okay.
-She has a boyfriend.

44:45.891 --> 44:47.226
This is ridiculous.

44:48.352 --> 44:50.437
-We didn't know that.
-What do we do?

44:50.521 --> 44:52.189
Good God…

44:59.279 --> 45:01.240
Just a little more. Just over there.

45:02.282 --> 45:03.492
Oh God!

45:10.749 --> 45:12.418
God, you're killing me.

45:21.927 --> 45:22.845
JJONG

45:26.724 --> 45:28.976
Yes. I'm answering for Ms. Yun.

45:29.059 --> 45:31.854
Did something happen to Song?

45:33.147 --> 45:36.066
She received an award
and got drunk at the after-party.

45:36.150 --> 45:37.901
But she's somewhere safe now?

45:37.985 --> 45:40.988
Yes. She's back in her room, sleeping.

45:41.071 --> 45:43.991
So you brought her back. Thank you.

45:44.074 --> 45:47.745
Sure. But who am I speaking to?

45:47.828 --> 45:49.496
Oh, I didn't even introduce myself.

45:49.580 --> 45:52.332
I'm Song's boyfriend.

45:53.500 --> 45:54.710
What?

45:54.793 --> 45:57.171
I'm the person who's dating Song.

45:57.254 --> 45:58.088
Oh my.

45:59.757 --> 46:02.301
I'm sorry.
I didn't think you'd be her boyfriend.

46:02.384 --> 46:05.179
It's been a while,
but I guess she hasn't told anyone yet.

46:05.262 --> 46:08.098
Anyway, thank you for today.

46:08.640 --> 46:10.851
No problem. Good night.

46:22.446 --> 46:25.365
So she was telling the truth
about having a boyfriend?

46:27.951 --> 46:30.454
Did you put her to bed?
You are coming back, right?

46:30.537 --> 46:32.372
We're going for round two!

46:32.873 --> 46:33.999
I'm coming over now.

46:37.419 --> 46:38.754
Mr. Park.

46:38.837 --> 46:42.007
How long have you been close with Hwany?

46:43.634 --> 46:45.803
-Who says we're close?
-What?

46:46.762 --> 46:47.596
You're so funny!

46:49.181 --> 46:51.433
We are close.
This guy can't live without me.

46:51.517 --> 46:53.185
I wouldn't say that.

47:16.875 --> 47:17.709
JI-YEON

47:17.793 --> 47:21.630
Business trip's boring, huh?
Want to hear how my blind date went?

47:23.006 --> 47:24.591
She just won't stop.

47:27.469 --> 47:29.179
Nope.

47:43.026 --> 47:46.154
Hey, I'll give you ten seconds.
Out with it.

47:47.531 --> 47:49.199
Come on. Ten seconds is too short.

47:51.451 --> 47:52.286
What?

47:53.078 --> 47:54.121
How did…

47:54.204 --> 47:57.291
I got your car fixed,
so I wanted to take you for a drive.

47:57.791 --> 47:58.792
Where are you?

48:00.460 --> 48:02.296
I can't go right now.

48:02.379 --> 48:03.213
Why is that?

48:04.798 --> 48:07.634
I hear waves.
I'm also at the beach right now.

48:07.718 --> 48:09.386
I'll head over to you, then.

48:10.554 --> 48:12.723
And how are you gonna do that?

48:13.223 --> 48:15.058
Why do you think I can't?

48:18.729 --> 48:20.564
How would he come here?

48:21.732 --> 48:23.150
Who does he think he's kidding?

49:13.408 --> 49:14.868
You actually made it?

49:27.714 --> 49:28.924
So warm.

49:44.106 --> 49:45.399
What are you doing here?

49:49.653 --> 49:50.487
Hello?

49:51.697 --> 49:52.781
Hello?

50:14.636 --> 50:16.430
Oh God! That hurts.

50:16.513 --> 50:21.476
My mom wanted me to become a doctor
ever since I was little.

50:21.560 --> 50:23.895
I somehow managed to get through division,

50:23.979 --> 50:25.731
but I got stuck at fractions.

50:25.814 --> 50:27.983
This is going to sting. There.

50:28.066 --> 50:30.736
Goodness, it's okay. It's only a dream.

50:31.737 --> 50:32.821
Hey, you!

50:38.201 --> 50:40.328
Who is this hottie?

50:40.412 --> 50:41.621
Nice.

50:41.705 --> 50:43.540
Get a grip, will you?

50:43.623 --> 50:45.459
This is such a weird dream.

50:46.460 --> 50:48.378
-What?
-This has to be a dream.

50:48.462 --> 50:50.130
-Isn't this a dream?
-What now?

50:53.341 --> 50:54.926
-It actually hurts.
-Move.

51:14.404 --> 51:15.655
Who the heck is this?

51:16.656 --> 51:19.576
Hand over the paper in the drawer,
and I'll spare your life.

51:20.786 --> 51:23.497
Yeah. I get what's going on here.

51:24.081 --> 51:25.749
I'm glad you catch on quickly.

51:33.965 --> 51:36.635
That's strange.
Someone should be here to save me by now.

51:36.718 --> 51:38.136
-Wait. Unhand me!
-Hello?

51:38.220 --> 51:39.638
Is my boyfriend out there?

51:46.436 --> 51:47.771
My lady!

51:47.854 --> 51:48.855
My lady!

51:49.523 --> 51:50.774
You scoundrel!

51:53.276 --> 51:54.111
Dolsoe?

51:54.736 --> 51:56.822
My lady! You bastard!

51:57.322 --> 51:58.865
-Dolsoe!
-What the…

51:59.449 --> 52:00.534
Yes!

53:09.728 --> 53:14.733
Subtitle translation by: Daham Yoon
